ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ValueRange: Hispanic or Latino; Not Hispanic or Latino; Unknown
American Indian/Alaska Native; Asian; Hawaiian or Pacific Islander; Black or African American; White; More than one race; Unknown or not reported; Other Non-White; Other

ElementDescription: Recruited for DCF or control group?

Notes: 0= Birth parent; 1= Foster parent; 2= Grandparent; 3= Other relative, 4= Residential center; 5= Other; 999= Not Answered

ElementDescription: If "other" for previous question, please describe
Social status code as calculated from Parent CARE form
Number of years in formal education

Notes: R = Right; L = Left; B = Both; 999= No Answer; 888= Skipped; 777= Condition Skipped; 555= Missing

1=Unemployed (no school or work activity); on disability; homemaker w/ no dependent children (or other family member) in need of daily care-taking; or day program/day hospital attendance only; 2=Volunteer or temp job; sheltered or competitive part-time employment (<20 hrs/wk); full-time mother/father/caretaker of children (or other family member) in need of daily care-taking (e.g., a full-time stay-at-home mom); or part-time student; 3=Competitive employment (20+ hrs/wk); or multiple part-time jobs (20+ hrs/wk); or full-time student
1=Correctional Facility;   2=Homeless Shelter; 3=Treatment Institution; 4=Supervised Facility; 5=Supervised Non-Facility;   6=Assisted/Supported; 7=Independent Living

ElementDescription: Tohen Modified Location Code Index. If multiple ratings possible, choose highest rating.
Notes: 0 = Unknown or Missing; 1 = Head of household or functional household member;  2 = Alone or with peer; (also, living in a rented room);  3 = With family member under minimal supervision;  4 = Unsupervised boarding home; (also, college dorm or military barracks);  5 = Cooperative apartment; 6 = Halfway house; 7 = With family member under close supervision; 8 = Open quarter-way house OR transitional care unit on hospital grounds; 9 = Hospitalized OR Homeless

ElementDescription: Tohen Modified Vocational Status Index. If multiple ratings possible, choose highest rating
Notes: 0 = Unknown or Missing;  1 = Full-time gainful employment;  2 = Full-time student OR homemaker OR mother/father/other caretaker of children (or other family member) in need of daily care-taking (e.g. full-time "stay-at-home mom");  3 = Part-time student OR part-time gainful employment (30 hrs/wk or less);  4 = Retired;  5 = Full- or part-time volunteer;  6 = On medical or psychiatric leave of absence;  7 = Unemployed (whether or not expected to work)

1=Never Attended School (=0 years); 2=Some Grade School (=1-7 years); 3=Completed Grade School (=8 years); 4=Some High School (=9-11 years); 5=Completed High School (=12 years); 6=Completed Vocational / Trade / Technical School -OR- G.E.D. (=12 years, unless another # of years is specified); 7=Some College (=13-15 years); 8=Completed College (=16 years); 9=Some Graduate School (=17 years); 10=Completed Graduate School (=18+ years)

ElementDescription: Does the child have any brothers and sisters with whom she/he does not live with?
Participant's 'Current Care Setting,' At Time of Screening Visit
Notes: 1=Inpatient (=inpatient hospitalization); 2=Outpatient (=rehabilitation program or PRP); 3=Day Hospital (=day hospital); 4=Other (=less level of care, i.e. an outpatient doctor)

ElementDescription: Is teen currently enrolled in school? (alternatively, does teen plan to return to school when it resumes)
Notes: 0= No; 1= Yes; 2= Yes, college; 3= Yes, high school
